<p>Aristotle</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8dt"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8dt" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8dt')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8dt" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8dt')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8dt" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8dt?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8dt" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8dt')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8dt class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8dt" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_8dt" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_8dt" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8rj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8rj" class="parent"><a name="8rj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8rj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8rj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8rj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/pangloss/">pangloss</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 01:09:15AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8rj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8rj')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8rj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8rj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/pangloss/">pangloss</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 01:09:15AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8rj'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8rj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8rj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8rj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That is an interesting contrast with Spinoza's view that all ideas enter the mind as beliefs, and that mere apprehension is achieved by diminishing something about the idea believed.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8rj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8rj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8rj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8rj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8rj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8rj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8rj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8rj" href="#8dt" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8rj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8rj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8rj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8rj" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_8rj" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_8rj" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8ul" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8ul" class="parent"><a name="8ul" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8ul" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8ul" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8ul" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 11:34:30AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ul'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8ul')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8ul" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8ul" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 11:34:30AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8ul'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ul'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8ul')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8ul" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I don't think it's a <em>contrast</em>. The point is that it takes practice to do the necessary diminishing.</p>

<p>Spinoza was ahead of his time: there's more recent psychological research confirming that when you hear a statement -- even if the context makes it clear that no one is seriously telling you it's true -- the effect is to make you believe it more; and that this effect is stronger if you're having to use more of your brain for some other task at the same time. I forget all the details, but I think there was some discussion of this on Overcoming Bias 6-18 months ago (90% confidence interval).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8ul"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8ul" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ul')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8ul" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ul')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8ul" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8ul?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8ul" href="#8rj" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8ul" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8ul')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8ul class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8ul" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_8ul" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_8ul" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8w5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8w5" class="parent"><a name="8w5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8w5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8w5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8w5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/pangloss/">pangloss</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 02:26:37PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8w5'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8w5')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8w5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8w5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/pangloss/">pangloss</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">21 April 2009 02:26:37PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8w5'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8w5'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8w5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8w5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Oh, that's a good point.  I was assuming Aristotle was commending people who could hear it without coming to believe it, but it could easily be that he is commending people who diminish their belief rapidly, and acquire a state of mere apprehension.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8w5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8w5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8w5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8w5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8w5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8w5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8w5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8w5" href="#8ul" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8w5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8w5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8w5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8w5" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8dz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8dz" class="parent"><a name="8dz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8dz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8dz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8dz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 01:07:40AM</span><span class="votes " >13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8dz'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8dz')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8dz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8dz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 01:07:40AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8dz'>13 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8dz'] = ['12 points', '13 points', '14 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8dz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8dz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Most things are, in fact, slippery slopes. And if you start backing off from one thing because it's a slippery slope, who knows where you'll stop?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Sean M Burke</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8dz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8dz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8dz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8dz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8dz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8dz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8dz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8dz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8dz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8dz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8dz" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8cm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8cm" class="parent"><a name="8cm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8cm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8cm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8cm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Furcas/">Furcas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 10:11:19PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >16 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8cm'] = ['15 points', '16 points', '17 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8cm')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8cm" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8cm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Furcas/">Furcas</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 10:11:19PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8cm'>16 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8cm'] = ['15 points', '16 points', '17 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8cm')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8cm" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>When two opposite points of view are expressed with equal intensity, the truth does not necessarily lie exactly halfway between them. It is possible for one side to be simply wrong.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Richard Dawkins</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8cm"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8cm" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8cm')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8cm" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8cm')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8cm" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8cm?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8cm" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8cm')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8cm class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8cm" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8e1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8e1" class="parent"><a name="8e1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8e1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8e1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8e1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 01:10:57AM</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8e1'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8e1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8e1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8e1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 01:10:57AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8e1'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8e1'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8e1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8e1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Truth emerges much more readily from error than from confusion.</p>
