 '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8ci')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8ci" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>The man of science, whatever his hopes may be, must lay them aside while he studies nature; and the philosopher, if he is to achieve truth, must do the same. Ethical considerations can only legitimately appear when the truth has been ascertained: they can and should appear as determining our feeling towards the truth, and our manner of ordering our lives in view of the truth, but not as themselves dictating what the truth is to be.</p>
