;</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2542')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2542" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I remember someone on slashdot replied to that quote by saying, basically, If you're a mid-19th century member of Parliament, and you're presented with a machine design you don't understand (and don't expect to), by a respectable person asking for money, but you have a basically non-mysterious view of the world, what kinds of questions <em>can</em> you ask to determine whether the idea is scam?  The question Babbage complains about is an excellent one.</p>

