" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>"[T]he purpose of writing is to inflate weak ideas, obscure poor reasoning, and inhibit clarity." - Calvin, Bill Watterson's "Calvin and Hobbes"</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8au"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8au" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8au')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8au" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8au')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8au" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8au?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8au" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8au')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8au class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8au" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8d2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8d2" class="parent"><a name="8d2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8d2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8d2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8d2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 11:04:30PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8d2'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8d2')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8d2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8d2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 11:04:30PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8d2'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8d2'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8d2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8d2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Fifth and last.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Don't learn tricks, learn juggling.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Anon</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8d2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8d2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8d2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8d2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8d2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8d2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8d2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8d2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8d2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8d2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8d2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_8d2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_8d2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8ft" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8ft" class="parent"><a name="8ft" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8ft" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8ft" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8ft" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 08:52:47AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ft'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8ft')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8ft" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8ft" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 08:52:47AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8ft'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ft'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8ft')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8ft" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>As this got voted down, perhaps some commentary is in order. This quote is from a juggling forum a long time ago, and is in fact about juggling. But I also read it as a parallel of the twelfth <a href="http://yudkowsky.net/rational/virtues" rel="nofollow">virtue of rationality</a>.</p>

<p>The juggler's task is to entertain his audience, and if he fails, it is futile for him to protest that he can do many tricks. It is not enough to master many techniques. They must be used to achieve the result that the techniques aim at.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8ft"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8ft" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ft')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8ft" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ft')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8ft" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8ft?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8ft" href="#8d2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8ft" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8ft')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8ft class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8ft" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8ao" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8ao" class="parent"><a name="8ao" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8ao" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8ao" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8ao" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelGR/">MichaelGR</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 07:04:05PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ao'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8ao')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8ao" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8ao" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MichaelGR/">MichaelGR</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 07:04:05PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8ao'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ao'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8ao')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8ao" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Protein engineering is often approached as if it were part of biology. Imagine approaching aerospace engineering as if it were part of ornithology: Although the pioneers of human flight learned a lot about wings from birds, if they had waited for success in making artificial feathers and artificial muscle, we’d still be on the ground.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>--<a href="http://metamodern.com/2009/03/30/a-revolution-in-de-novo-protein-engineering/" rel="nofollow">K. Eric Drexler</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8ao"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8ao" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ao')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8ao" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ao')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8ao" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8ao?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8ao" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8ao')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8ao class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8ao" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8dr" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8dr" class="parent"><a name="8dr" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8dr" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8dr" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8dr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 12:58:25AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8dr'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8dr')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8dr" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8dr" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 12:58:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8dr'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8dr'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#"