</blockquote>

<p>-- Bruce Henderson</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_88x"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_88x" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_88x')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_88x" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_88x')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_88x" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/88x?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_88x" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_88x')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_88x class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_88x" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_88x" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_88x" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_89i" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_89i" class="parent"><a name="89i" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_89i" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_89i" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_89i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 02:35:20PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89i'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_89i')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_89i" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_89i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 02:35:20PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_89i'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89i'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_89i')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_89i" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The citation is taken from "<a href="http://www.bcg.com/publications/files/Eng11Brinkmanship.pdf" rel="nofollow">Brinkmanship in Business</a>"[pdf]. The cited assertion is actually a mistake, as it presupposes that the right thing to do in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimatum_game" rel="nofollow">Ultimatum game</a> is to accept any amount offered to you, and never punish the unfair dealer. The whole document is a lesson in Dark Arts.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_89i"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_89i" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89i')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_89i" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89i')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_89i" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/89i?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_89i" href="#88x" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_89i" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_89i')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_89i class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_89i" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_89i" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_89i" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_89n" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_89n" class="parent"><a name="89n" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_89n" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_89n" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_89n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:00:21PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_89n')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_89n" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_89n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:00:21PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_89n'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_89n')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_89n" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I posted the quote half hoping for a response like this. I have only superficial knowledge of  Newcomb's Problem, and knew this would be relevant. I wrote "Rationalists should WIN!" in the margin of the article.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The whole document is a lesson in Dark Arts</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Please taboo "Dark Arts".</p>

<p>Also note that the competitor in this context is an industrial company, in a pre-Silicon Valley era. They have to restrain their (price) competition, or they will destroy each other. The question is how to make the competitor restrain himself more than you do.  To me this looks more like capitalism than The Villain's Handbook.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_89n"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_89n" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89n')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_89n" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89n')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_89n" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/89n?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_89n" href="#89i" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_89n" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_89n')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_89n class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_89n" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_89n" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_89n" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_89q" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_89q" class="parent"><a name="89q" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_89q" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_89q" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_89q" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:23:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89q'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_89q')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_89q" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_89q" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:23:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_89q'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89q'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_89q')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_89q" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Please taboo "Dark Arts".</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I like the phrase. The document is written to profess a mistaken position about how to deceive, and as a result it becomes a deceptive lesson in deception, <a href="http://www.overcomingbias.com/2008/10/the-dark-side.html">Dark Side Epistemology</a> incarnate.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_89q"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_89q" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89q')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_89q" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89q')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_89q" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/89q?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_89q" href="#89n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_89q" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_89q')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_89q class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_89q" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_89q" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_89q" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_89t" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_89t" class="parent"><a name="89t" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_89t" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_89t" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_89t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:58:52PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89t'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_89t')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_89t" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_89t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 03:58:52PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_89t'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89t'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_89t')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_89t" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Oh, <em>those</em> Dark Arts. Now I <em>should</em> thoroughly re-read that article with a proper understanding of Newcomb's Problem. But I ain't gonna do that. Although I have some doubt about your use of the Ultimatum game here, I will just defer to your judgment and reduce my confidence in Henderson as a business thinker from 90% to 70% in context, and an additional 20% for being outdated.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_89t"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_89t" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89t')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_89t" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89t')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_89t" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/89t?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_89t" href="#89q" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_89t" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_89t')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_89t class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_89t" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_89t" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_89t" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_89w" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_89w" class="parent"><a name="89w" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_89w" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_89w" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_89w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 04:19:06PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89w'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_89w')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_89w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_89w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 04:19:06PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_89w'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_89w'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_89w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_89w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>No, he might be right about how people in business react "rationally", and I wouldn't know anything about <em>that</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_89w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_89w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_89w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_89w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_89w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/89w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_89w" href="#89t" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_89w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_89w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_89w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_89w" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_89w" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_89w" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8fv" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8fv" class="parent"><a name="8fv" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8fv" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8fv" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8fv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 09:25:16AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8fv'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8fv')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8fv" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8fv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Stefan_King/">Stefan_King</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 09:25:16AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8fv'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8fv'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8fv')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8fv" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Now you lost me. According to you, is the document a deceptive lesson in deception or not? If it is, one should reduce confidence in Henderson. If it is not, what is your point, what is the mistake you see?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8fv"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8fv" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8fv')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8fv" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8fv')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8fv" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8fv?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8fv" href="#89w" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8fv" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8fv')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8fv class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8fv" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_8fv" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_8fv" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_8ga" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_8ga" class="parent"><a name="8ga" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_8ga" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_8ga" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_8ga" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 12:12:35PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ga'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_8ga')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_8ga" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_8ga" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 April 2009 12:12:35PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_8ga'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_8ga'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_8ga')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_8ga" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>You may give solid advice, accompanying it with ridiculous <a href="http://www.overcomingbias.com/2007/09/rationalization.html">rationalization</a>. The <a href="http://www.overcomingbias.com/2007/09/the-bottom-line.html">bottom line</a> is correct, but the reasons you put above it are not. So, in this case, I assume that the practical advice he gives <em>might</em> be reasonable, but the description of why it works is not.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_8ga"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_8ga" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ga')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_8ga" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_8ga')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_8ga" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/bs/rationality_quotes_april_2009/8ga?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_8ga" href="#8fv" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_8ga" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_8ga')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_8ga class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_8ga" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_88d" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_88d" class="parent"><a name="88d" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_88d" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_88d" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_88d" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Z_M_Davis/">Z_M_Davis</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 April 2009 05:39:26AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">